<TITLE> One dead, 20 hurt in Comilla train collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, July 25 (bdnews24.com) - One passenger was killed and 20 others injured when two trains collided head-on at Laksham junction in Comilla Friday, a Bangladesh Railway statement said Friday. The deceased was identified as Md Mainuddin, son of Abdul Karim of Peergachha in Rangpur district, according to the statement. Two deaths had earlier been reported in the accident. The injured were admitted to Laksham and Comilla general hospitals. Train movement on the Dhaka-Chittagong line was uninterrupted after the incident, the railway authorities said. The press statement said the inter-city Upokul Express and a local train collided head on at Laksham junction, derailing two carriages of the express train. Laksham station master Masdhusudhan Chowdhury said a train heading to Noakhali from Dhaka and another going to Akhaura from Chittagong collided as they were both entering the junction at around 12.30pm. "The accident occurred due to a faulty signal," said the station master. Meanwhile, the railway authorities said a four-member probe committee had been formed to discover the cause of the accident. Communications secretary Mahbubur Rahman and Comilla deputy commissioner Md Monzurur Rahman visited the spot. bdnews24.com/c
